# Product Operating Model Playbook

A framework for how product organizations operate and deliver outcomes.

The product operating model defines how product teams structure work, make decisions, and collaborate across the organization.

---

# Purpose

The goal of a product operating model is to create clarity around:

• product team structure  
• decision authority  
• planning processes  
• delivery workflows  

---

# The Product Operating System

Modern product teams operate across four core activities.

Strategy  
↓  
Discovery  
↓  
Delivery  
↓  
Learning  

This continuous cycle drives product improvement.

---

# Strategy

Defines long-term direction.

Activities include:

• product vision  
• strategic planning  
• roadmap definition  

---

# Discovery

Validates problems and opportunities before building.

Activities include:

• user research  
• prototype testing  
• opportunity assessment  

Discovery reduces risk before investment.

---

# Delivery

Execution of product initiatives.

Activities include:

• product development  
• sprint planning  
• feature launches  

Delivery turns validated opportunities into shipped products.

---

# Learning

Continuous improvement based on real-world feedback.

Activities include:

• analytics  
• experimentation  
• user feedback  

Learning informs the next strategy cycle.

---

# Product Team Structure

Modern product teams are typically organized as cross-functional squads.

A typical product team includes:

• Product Manager  
• Engineering Lead  
• Designers  
• Data / Analytics  

Teams should be empowered to solve problems within defined strategic boundaries.

---

# Governance and Alignment

Product leadership ensures alignment through regular forums.

Common mechanisms include:

• product reviews  
• roadmap reviews  
• strategic planning cycles  

These maintain alignment between teams and company goals.
